modules.description: Creates and manages socket endpoints with explicit domain and type parameters, supporting IPv6 multicast configurations. Operates on domain-specific and type-specific representations to enforce network protocol constraints. Used to establish communication channels for sending and receiving multicast data over IPv6 networks.

Sets socket options for IPv6 multicast configurations, including controls for joining groups and managing traffic delivery. Operates on socket descriptors and specific multicast-related option types. Used to configure sockets for efficient group communication in network applications.

Provides functions to join and leave IPv6 multicast groups, manage multicast interface indices, and set loopback options. Operates on socket file descriptors, IPv6 addresses, and interface identifiers. Used to configure network applications for efficient multicast traffic reception and control.

Establishes and configures IPv6 multicast sockets through domain- and type-specific socket creation and option setting. Manages group membership and traffic control using socket descriptors and multicast-specific parameters. Enables sending and receiving multicast data over IPv6 networks with precise configuration. Examples include joining a multicast group, setting time-to-live values, and binding to a specific interface for targeted data reception.
